 the vendor. On the other hand, on-premise solutions give you complete control over your data and customization options. Each model has its own specific benefits for yard operations, such as gate automation and asset tracking.",[2290],{"type":149,"attrs":2291},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2293,"content":2294},{"textAlign":139},[2295],{"text":2296,"type":75,"marks":2297},"In this comparison, we will explore the practical effects of choosing between cloud-based and on-premise yard management software solutions. Our goal is to help you make a well-informed decision that aligns with your operational requirements.",[2298],{"type":149,"attrs":2299},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2301,"content":2302},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2303],{"text":2304,"type":75,"marks":2305},"Understanding Yard Management Software (YMS)",[2306,2308],{"type":149,"attrs":2307},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2310,"content":2311},{"textAlign":139},[2312],{"text":2313,"type":75,"marks":2314},"Yard Management Software (YMS) is a crucial tool for logistics facilities. It helps manage the movement of trailers, containers, and equipment in your yard. Instead of chaotic operations, YMS brings order and visibility to your yard. You can easily track your assets, know their locations, and plan the next steps.",[2315],{"type":149,"attrs":2316},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2318,"content":2319},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2320],{"text":2321,"type":75,"marks":2322},"The Evolution of Yard Management Software",[2323,2325],{"type":149,"attrs":2324},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2327,"content":2328},{"textAlign":139},[2329,2334,2340,2345,2351],{"text":2330,"type":75,"marks":2331},"In the past, YMS solutions mainly focused on basic tracking and manual processes. However, modern platforms like ",[2332],{"type":149,"attrs":2333},{"color":2236},{"text":2335,"type":75,"marks":2336},"Terminal Industries' AI-native Yard Operating System™",[2337,2339],{"type":149,"attrs":2338},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2341,"type":75,"marks":2342}," are revolutionizing yard operations. This new approach combines computer vision technology with real-time data infrastructure to achieve ",[2343],{"type":149,"attrs":2344},{"color":2236},{"text":2346,"type":75,"marks":2347},"99.5% data accuracy",[2348,2350],{"type":149,"attrs":2349},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2352,"type":75,"marks":2353}," without the need for manual scans or GPS devices on every asset.",[2354],{"type":149,"attrs":2355},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2357,"content":2358},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2359],{"text":2360,"type":75,"marks":2361},"How YMS Improves Yard Efficiency",[2362,2364],{"type":149,"attrs":2363},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2366,"content":2367},{"textAlign":139},[2368],{"text":2369,"type":75,"marks":2370},"Yard efficiency improves through three key capabilities:",[2371],{"type":149,"attrs":2372},{"color":2236},{"type":1340,"content":2374},[2375,2391,2407],{"type":1299,"content":2376},[2377],{"type":112,"attrs":2378,"content":2379},{"textAlign":139},[2380,2386],{"text":2381,"type":75,"marks":2382},"Automation",[2383,2385],{"type":149,"attrs":2384},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2387,"type":75,"marks":2388},": Terminal Industries' SmartYard™ enables automated gate processes that reduce transaction times by over 85%, allowing your team to process more vehicles with fewer errors.",[2389],{"type":149,"attrs":2390},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":2392},[2393],{"type":112,"attrs":2394,"content":2395},{"textAlign":139},[2396,2402],{"text":2397,"type":75,"marks":2398},"Digitization",[2399,2401],{"type":149,"attrs":2400},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2403,"type":75,"marks":2404},": You gain instant visibility into asset locations, zone capacity, and movement history without walking the yard or relying on outdated spreadsheets.",[2405],{"type":149,"attrs":2406},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":2408},[2409],{"type":112,"attrs":2410,"content":2411},{"textAlign":139},[2412,2418],{"text":2413,"type":75,"marks":2414},"Real-time data",[2415,2417],{"type":149,"attrs":2416},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2419,"type":75,"marks":2420},": When your system knows which trailers need to move, where they're going, and what's blocking them, you can orchestrate yard operations that prevent bottlenecks before they form.",[2421],{"type":149,"attrs":2422},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2424,"content":2425},{"textAlign":139},[2426],{"text":2427,"type":75,"marks":2428},"This level of operational insight drives throughput improvements exceeding 50% in many facilities.",[2429],{"type":149,"attrs":2430},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2432,"content":2433},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2434],{"text":2435,"type":75,"marks":2436},"Deployment Models for Yard Management Software",[2437,2439],{"type":149,"attrs":2438},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2441,"content":2442},{"textAlign":139},[2443],{"text":2444,"type":75,"marks":2445},"When evaluating deployment options for your yard management system, you'll encounter two primary software hosting models that fundamentally shape how you implement and operate your solution.",[2446],{"type":149,"attrs":2447},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2449,"content":2450},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2451],{"text":2452,"type":75,"marks":2453},"1. Cloud-Based YMS Solutions",[2454,2456],{"type":149,"attrs":2455},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2458,"content":2459},{"textAlign":139},[2460],{"text":2461,"type":75,"marks":2462},"Cloud-based YMS platforms run on vendor-managed servers accessible through the internet. You access the software through web browsers or mobile applications without installing hardware or maintaining physical infrastructure at your facility. The vendor handles all server maintenance, security updates, and system upgrades on their end. Your data resides in secure data centers managed by the software provider, with automatic backups and redundancy built into the service model. Terminal's Yard Operating System™ exemplifies this approach with its cloud-native architecture, enabling rapid deployment through the Terminal-in-a-Camera™ hardware kit that requires minimal on-site installation.",[2463],{"type":149,"attrs":2464},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2466,"content":2467},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2468],{"text":2469,"type":75,"marks":2470},"2. On-Premise YMS Solutions",[2471,2473],{"type":149,"attrs":2472},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2475,"content":2476},{"textAlign":139},[2477],{"text":2478,"type":75,"marks":2479},"On-premise systems require you to install and maintain software on servers located at your facilities. You purchase licenses upfront and assume responsibility for hardware procurement, system configuration, and ongoing maintenance. Your IT team manages updates, security patches, and data backups. The software and all operational data remain within your physical infrastructure, giving you direct control over every aspect of the system environment.",[2480],{"type":149,"attrs":2481},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2483,"content":2484},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2485],{"text":2486,"type":75,"marks":2487},"Key Differences in Operation",[2488,2490],{"type":149,"attrs":2489},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2492,"content":2493},{"textAlign":139},[2494],{"text":2495,"type":75,"marks":2496},"The hosting model determines who controls your infrastructure. Cloud solutions shift maintenance responsibilities to the vendor, while on-premise setups require dedicated IT resources. Accessibility varies significantly—cloud platforms enable remote access from any internet-connected device, whereas on-premise systems typically restrict access to your local network unless you configure VPN connections. Control over customization and data storage represents another critical distinction, with on-premise solutions offering deeper system-level modifications at the cost of increased complexity.",[2497],{"type":149,"attrs":2498},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2500,"content":2501},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2502],{"text":2503,"type":75,"marks":2504},"Advantages of Cloud-Based Yard Management Software",[2505,2507],{"type":149,"attrs":2506},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2509,"content":2510},{"textAlign":139},[2511],{"text":2512,"type":75,"marks":2513},"Cloud-based yard management software delivers immediate value through rapid deployment capabilities that eliminate lengthy installation processes. You can have your system operational within hours rather than weeks or months. Terminal's Yard Operating System™ exemplifies this approach with its Terminal-in-a-Camera™ hardware kit—a plug-and-play unit that requires no trenching or extensive infrastructure modifications. This vendor-managed infrastructure means you bypass the traditional IT burden of server procurement, network configuration, and hardware maintenance.",[2514],{"type":149,"attrs":2515},{"color":2236},{"type":1295,"attrs":2517,"content":2518},{"order":71},[2519],{"type":1299,"content":2520},[2521],{"type":112,"attrs":2522},{"textAlign":139},{"type":69,"attrs":2524,"content":2525},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2526],{"text":2527,"type":75,"marks":2528},"Scalability",[2529,2531],{"type":149,"attrs":2530},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":2533,"content":2534},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2535],{"text":2536,"type":75,"marks":2537},"Scalability becomes a natural extension of your operations rather than a capital-intensive project. When you need to expand from five warehouses to fifteen, cloud-based solutions grow with you. You add new locations to your network without purchasing additional servers or hiring specialized IT staff. The subscription pricing model transforms major capital expenditures into predictable operational expenses, making budget planning straightforward and eliminating the financial shock of hardware refresh cycles.",[2538],{"type":149,"attrs":2539},{"color":2540},"#434343",{"type":69,"attrs":2542,"content":2543},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2544],{"text":2545,"type":75,"marks":2546},"2. Multi-site management",[2547,2549],{"type":149,"attrs":2548},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2551,"content":2552},{"textAlign":139},[2553],{"text":2554,"type":75,"marks":2555},"Multi-site management reaches new levels of efficiency through unified dashboards that provide single-pane-of-glass visibility across your entire yard network. You monitor asset movements, gate activities, and operational metrics from any location with internet access. Real-time remote access means your logistics team coordinates activities across multiple facilities simultaneously, responding to disruptions or opportunities as they emerge.",[2556],{"type":149,"attrs":2557},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2559,"content":2560},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2561],{"text":2562,"type":75,"marks":2563},"3.Integration Capabilities ",[2564,2566],{"type":149,"attrs":2565},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":2568},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},{"type":69,"attrs":2570,"content":2571},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[2572],{"text":2573,"type":75,"marks":2574},"Integration capabilities set cloud-based systems apart in today's interconnected supply chain environment. You connect seamlessly with your existing ERP, TMS, and IoT devices, creating end-to-end visibility from gate to dock. These integrations happen through modern APIs rather than custom coding projects. Automatic updates arrive without downtime or manual intervention, ensuring you always operate with the latest features, security patches, and performance improvements.",[2575],{"type":149,"attrs":2576},{"color":2540},{"type":69,"attrs":2578,"content":2579},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2580],{"text":2581,"type":75,"marks":2582},"Benefits of On-Premise Yard Management Software Solutions",[2583,2585],{"type":149,"attrs":2584},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2587,"content":2588},{"textAlign":139},[2589,2594,2600],{"text":2590,"type":75,"marks":2591},"On-premise yard management software delivers ",[2592],{"type":149,"attrs":2593},{"color":2236},{"text":2595,"type":75,"marks":2596},"data control",[2597,2599],{"type":149,"attrs":2598},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2601,"type":75,"marks":2602}," that appeals to organizations with stringent security requirements or regulatory constraints. You maintain complete ownership of your data infrastructure, storing sensitive information about shipments, carriers, and yard operations within your own servers. This level of control becomes particularly valuable when you're handling proprietary logistics processes or operating in industries with strict data residency requirements.",[2603],{"type":149,"attrs":2604},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2606,"content":2607},{"textAlign":139},[2608,2614],{"text":2609,"type":75,"marks":2610},"Customization",[2611,2613],{"type":149,"attrs":2612},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2615,"type":75,"marks":2616}," reaches its full potential with on-premise deployments. You can modify the software architecture to align precisely with your unique yard workflows, integrate deeply with legacy systems, and build custom modules that address specific operational challenges. Organizations with complex yard operations—such as those managing specialized equipment or handling hazardous materials—benefit from this flexibility to create tailored solutions that cloud-based systems may not accommodate.",[2617],{"type":149,"attrs":2618},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2620,"content":2621},{"textAlign":139},[2622,2626,2632],{"text":1514,"type":75,"marks":2623},[2624],{"type":149,"attrs":2625},{"color":2236},{"text":2627,"type":75,"marks":2628},"offline functionality",[2629,2631],{"type":149,"attrs":2630},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2633,"type":75,"marks":2634}," of on-premise systems ensures your yard operations continue without interruption during internet outages or connectivity issues. Your gate processes, asset tracking, and yard management workflows remain operational regardless of external network status. This reliability proves critical for facilities in remote locations with unreliable internet infrastructure or operations that cannot afford any downtime due to connectivity problems.",[2635],{"type":149,"attrs":2636},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2638,"content":2639},{"textAlign":139},[2640],{"text":2641,"type":75,"marks":2642},"You also gain predictable long-term costs after the initial capital investment, avoiding ongoing subscription fees that can escalate as your operations scale.",[2643],{"type":149,"attrs":2644},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":2646,"content":2647},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2648],{"text":2649,"type":75,"marks":2650},"Key Differentiators: A Case Study on Terminal's AI-Native Yard Operating System™",[2651,2653],{"type":149,"attrs":2652},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2655,"content":2656},{"textAlign":139},[2657],{"text":2658,"type":75,"marks":2659},"Terminal's Yard Operating System™ demonstrates how cloud-based deployment unlocks capabilities that traditional on-premise solutions struggle to match. The platform's AI vision technology delivers 99.5% data accuracy through proprietary computer vision capabilities automatically tracking every asset movement without requiring manual scans or GPS devices.",[2660],{"type":149,"attrs":2661},{"color":2236},{"type":112,"attrs":2663,"content":2664},{"textAlign":139},[2665,2670,2676],{"text":2666,"type":75,"marks":2667},"The system's ",[2668],{"type":149,"attrs":2669},{"color":2236},{"text":2671,"type":75,"marks":2672},"SmartYard™ workflows",[2673,2675],{"type":149,"attrs":2674},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"text":2677,"type":75,"marks":2678}," transform gate operations from manual bottlenecks into automated processes. You can expect:",[2679],{"ty