rs":7650},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":7652,"content":7653},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[7654],{"text":7655,"type":75,"marks":7656},"How Automation is Changing Gate Operations",[7657,7659],{"type":149,"attrs":7658},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":7661,"content":7662},{"textAlign":139},[7663],{"text":7664,"type":75,"marks":7665},"The ability to automate certain processes is fundamentally changing how gates operate:",[7666],{"type":149,"attrs":7667},{"color":2236},{"type":1340,"content":7669},[7670,7680,7690],{"type":1299,"content":7671},[7672],{"type":112,"attrs":7673,"content":7674},{"textAlign":139},[7675],{"text":7676,"type":75,"marks":7677},"Computer vision technology can read license plates, container numbers, and seal IDs in just a few seconds. This replaces the old method of using clipboards and pens, which often leads to delays.",[7678],{"type":149,"attrs":7679},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":7681},[7682],{"type":112,"attrs":7683,"content":7684},{"textAlign":139},[7685],{"text":7686,"type":75,"marks":7687},"Dock assignments are now done automatically based on factors like load characteristics, carrier priorities, and available capacity.",[7688],{"type":149,"attrs":7689},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":7691},[7692],{"type":112,"attrs":7693,"content":7694},{"textAlign":139},[7695],{"text":7696,"type":75,"marks":7697},"Intelligent task dispatch engines are used to plan trailer movements in a way that avoids conflicts and maximizes efficiency.",[7698],{"type":149,"attrs":7699},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":7701,"content":7702},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[7703],{"text":7704,"type":75,"marks":7705},"The Importance of Real-Time Visibility",[7706,7708],{"type":149,"attrs":7707},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":7710,"content":7711},{"textAlign":139},[7712],{"text":7713,"type":75,"marks":7714},"One of the most important aspects of reducing idle time is having real-time visibility into operations:",[7715],{"type":149,"attrs":7716},{"color":2236},{"type":1340,"content":7718},[7719,7729,7739],{"type":1299,"content":7720},[7721],{"type":112,"attrs":7722,"content":7723},{"textAlign":139},[7724],{"text":7725,"type":75,"marks":7726},"Live dashboards show exactly where each asset is, how long it has been stationary, and when its next move is scheduled.",[7727],{"type":149,"attrs":7728},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":7730},[7731],{"type":112,"attrs":7732,"content":7733},{"textAlign":139},[7734],{"text":7735,"type":75,"marks":7736},"AI scheduling algorithms constantly update workflows as conditions change—such as late arrivals or priority shipments—to ensure everything runs smoothly.",[7737],{"type":149,"attrs":7738},{"color":2236},{"type":1299,"content":7740},[7741],{"type":112,"attrs":7742,"content":7743},{"textAlign":139},[7744],{"text":7745,"type":75,"marks":7746},"By being able to see potential congestion before it becomes a problem, you can redirect resources to prevent delays from spreading throughout your facility.",[7747],{"type":149,"attrs":7748},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":7750,"content":7751},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[7752],{"text":7753,"type":75,"marks":7754},"How Reducing Idle Time Leads to Lower Emissions and Sustainability Benefits",[7755,7757],{"type":149,"attrs":7756},{"color":2236},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":7759,"content":7760},{"textAlign":139},[7761],{"text":7762,"type":75,"marks":7763},"There is a clear and measurable link between idle time and reducing emissions. When trucks are stationary with their engines running, they are wasting fuel without doing any productive work—using about 0.8 gallons of fuel per hour while idling. By using a yard management system to reduce unnecessary waiting times, you can eliminate this waste and directly decrease the carbon footprint of your facility.",[7764],{"type":149,"attrs":7765},{"color":2236},{"type":69,"attrs":7767,"content":7768},{"level":1432,"textAlign":139},[7769],{"text":7770,"type":75,"m